        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> The key thing with horses is the buff on your buff bar. The effect of that buff is to activate your med skill while standing. It does not stack with arch-lich. Verant is quite wrong, per usual. It works 100% of the time, even while fighting and moving around.</P><P>Also, invis doesn't work with it. You'll get the invis icon, and mob will con indifferent, but will still aggro normally.</P><P>You can turn horse models off to get rid of the targeting problem, as well and ignore the spell/acceleration limitations. You can use Sow/jboots normally in this mode.</P><P>-------------<BR><b> <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=260982" target="_blank"> Malsheen</a></b><BR><font size=1><font color=gold>&lt;Bitter Monkeys&gt;</font id=gold><BR>  Rodcet Nife</font id=size1></font></td>
